Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a 
pinch of @salt{}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). 
Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed, no need to peel), then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways 
into small pieces. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). 
Peel the @potatoes{450%g}(peeled and sliced into 1cm rounds) and slice into 1cm wide rounds.

Pop the potato slices into your pan of boiling water, cook until just soft, 
~{12-15%minutes}.

> The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through, but be careful 
> because you don't want the slices to break up too much.

Once cooked, carefully drain in a #colander{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat. 
Add the @lamb mince{200%g}, cook until it has browned, ~{4-5%minutes}, breaking 
it up with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks. Add the onion and carrot and cook until 
soft, another ~{6%minutes}, stirring occasionally. Stir in the garlic and 
@dried oregano{1%tsp}, cook for ~{1%minute}, then add the @chopped tomatoes{1}(diced), 
@KNORR chicken stock{1}(chicken stock powder), @tomato puree{30%g} and @water{100%ml}. 
Add a pinch of @salt{}, @sugar{} and @pepper{}.

Bring the mixture to the boil, then simmer until thick and tomatoey, about 
~{10-14%minutes}. Stir occasionally. Meanwhile, pop the @soured cream{150%g} into a #bowl{}. 
Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}(grated) and add to the sour cream along 
with a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir together, set aside.

Once cooked, pour half the lamb mixture into an #oven dish{}, layer half the 
potatoes on top, pour over the remaining lamb mixture and spread it out with 
a #spoon{}. Layer over the remaining potatoes to cover the top. Spoon over 
the cheesy sour cream in dollops and spread it out with the back of a spoon. 
Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the top is golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

While the hotpot bakes, do the washing up. Once cooked, spoon the hotpot into 
#bowls{} and enjoy!